.TH pif-registry 1  "pif-registry " 
.SH NAME
pif\-registry \- Manage the local extension registry
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBpif\-registry\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Manage the local extension registry
.PP
pif records every extension it installs (name, version, install path). Use these subcommands to inspect or correct that record — for example after moving files manually or to force a clean reinstall.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
pif\-registry\-list(1)
Print all recorded extension installations
.TP
pif\-registry\-remove(1)
Remove a registry entry by extension name
.TP
pif\-registry\-clean(1)
Remove registry entries whose install paths no longer exist on disk
.TP
pif\-registry\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
